        <p>I tried various graphic cards, including a GeforceTI4200 and a Sapphire Radeon9600XT, all passively
            cooled. But since the AGP-slot of my motherboard doesn't seem to be able to give enough power, I had to
            ditch the latter. I have seen modifications to G4 cases which just stuck everything into the case
            without keeping the old layout. Those are of course not able to open the PC while running, which is the
            coolest effect of the G4 case.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <figure class="fig_right landscape dont_link">
            <img class="js-lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" data-original="/img/g4pc/g4_psu.jpg"/>
            <figcaption>The power supply.</figcaption>
