        <p class="clearfix">What good is a 420 Watt PSU with three silently running fans if one of them sucks the air from the wrong
        side of the case? Nothing, that's how good it would be. But this would have happened, if I installed my PSU
        the way Apple's PSU are installed with the power connectors beneath the fan outlet. So I had to do some more
        cutting to make room for the fan outlet and install the PSU upside-down. Now the third fan (which can be
        seen in the background on the left side of the picture) sucks the hot air right away from the cpu.</p>
    </section>

